<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>QSR Master Data Model Explorer</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js"></script>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@300;400;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    
    <!-- Chosen Palette: Warm Neutrals with Sky Blue and Amber Accents -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The application is structured as a two-part dashboard to optimize understanding of a technical document. Section 1 is an interactive 'Syndication Strategy' diagram built with HTML/CSS to explain the *purpose* (the 'Why'). Section 2 is a 'Document Explorer' that allows users to toggle between the 4 core JSON documents, viewing an explanatory summary, a visual data representation (Chart.js), and the raw JSON. This side-by-side logical grouping makes abstract data structures tangible and explorable. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
         - Syndication Strategy -> Goal: Inform/Flow -> Interactive HTML Cards -> Justification: Shows data movement without complex SVG diagrams.
         - Item Master -> Goal: Inform/Proportions -> Chart.js Doughnut -> Justification: Visualizes the recipe composition.
         - Modifier Groups -> Goal: Compare -> Chart.js Bar -> Justification: Compares price impacts of different modifiers.
         - Location Profiles -> Goal: Compare -> Chart.js Bar -> Justification: Clearly contrasts Base MSRP vs. Franchise Override Pricing.
         - Menu Catalogs -> Goal: Organize -> HTML Table/List -> Justification: Best for categorical, hierarchical data. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->

    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
            background-color: #f8fafc;
            color: #334155;
        }
        .chart-container {
            position: relative;
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 600px;
            margin-left: auto;
            margin-right: auto;
            height: 300px;
            max-height: 400px;
        }
        @media (min-width: 768px) {
            .chart-container {
                height: 350px;
            }
        }
        .json-viewer {
            font-family: monospace;
            white-space: pre-wrap;
            word-wrap: break-word;
        }
        .nav-button.active {
            background-color: #0ea5e9;
            color: white;
            border-color: #0ea5e9;
        }
        .nav-button {
            transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out;
        }
